<title>UK: ABI tumbles as sterling squeezes profits.</title>
<headline>ABI tumbles as sterling squeezes profits.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-08-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>ABI Leisure Group Plc shares dropped 23 percent on Tuesday after the company warned profits in the current year would fall short of analysts' expectations because of the continuing strength of sterling.</p>
<p>The stock closed 18p lower to 60.</p>
<p>&quot;Future  years' profitability could also be affected by exchange rates persisting at current levels,&quot; said chairman George Shiels.</p>
<p>&quot;However, the group is working to examine ways to minimise the effect of such exchange rates whilst remaining committed to its major position in the European market.&quot;</p>
<p>-- David Holmes, London Newsroom +44 171 542 4367</p>
